    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter" xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">Miklós Oláh to King Ferdinand I (Vienna, 1 February 1549)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">1. He received two letters from him yesterday: one on
                            his letter to Emperor Charles V on celebrating the ecumenical council
                            and the free confirmation of the prelates, and another that Oláh should
                            send Queen Isabella’s and George Martinuzzi’s letters back. He has
                            written to Pál Várday about the Pope’s confirmation of the prelates,
                            whose letter he attaches. One thing seems necessary, i.e. the King
                            should charge the Bishops of Nitra and Veszprém as well as Balázs
                            Péterváradi in a special letter with starting the process of ordination.
                            Oláh himself will receive the higher orders from the Bishop of Senj in
                            two days. 2. He should let him know what his plan is regarding Zsigmond
                            János so they can let the commissioners know when they go to Martinuzzi
                            on Saint Matthew’s day. He is expecting Tamás Nádasdy in two days, who
                            has been complaining to him about the lack of funds. It would be good if
                            by the time he got here, the King instructed the Chamber, if nothing
                            else works, to take care of his expenses.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Sacratissime Rex Domine, Domine mihi Clementissime, fidelitatis et
                    servitiorum meorum perpetuorum in gratiam Sacratissimae Maiestatis Vestrae
                    humillimam commendationem!</p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">[1.] Die hesterna binas Sacratissimae Maiestatis Vestrae accepi
                    litteras. Alteras<note type="critic" xml:id="note.1">See Ep.
                            707.<ref>olahus.tei.15490127_2</ref></note> de sacratissimae caesareae
                    maiestatis in promovenda apud summum dominum nostrum celebratione concilii
                    generalis et item confirmatione gratuita praelatorum Hungariae, singulari in rem
                    publicam Christianam clementia atque pio affectu. Alteras<note type="critic"
                        xml:id="note.2">See Ep. 706.<ref>olahus.tei.15490127_1</ref></note> vero,
                    quibus Sacratissima Maiestas Vestra iubet sibi quamprimum mitti acta legationis
                    serenissimae <persName>reginae Isabellae</persName> etc. et responsi
                    Sacratissimae Maiestatis Vestrae illi ac <persName>Fratri
                        Georgio</persName><note type="critic" xml:id="note.3">George
                        Martinuzzi.</note> aliisque nobilibus dati. Secundum Sacratissimae
                    Maiestatis Vestrae mandatum mitto nunc ad eam copiam praemissae et legationis et
                    responsi. De confirmatione autem apud summum pontificem praelatorum Hungariae
                    sollicitanda scripsi ad <persName>dominum Strigoniensem</persName>,<note
                        type="critic" xml:id="note.4">Pál Várday.</note> cui litteras etiam
                    Sacratissimae Maiestatis Vestrae misi.<note type="critic" xml:id="note.5">We do
                        not know these letters.</note> Unum tamen videtur esse necessarium, quod
                    Maiestas Vestra Sacratissima dignetur litteris suis mandare specialibus
                        Nittriensi,<note type="critic" xml:id="note.6">Ferenc Thurzó (†1576) was
                        Bishop of Nitra between 1534 and 1557. He was the President of the Hungarian
                        Chamber and the Court Chamber (1549–1563). For more see <hi rend="smallcap"
                            >Gecsényi</hi> 2010.</note> Vesprimiensi<note type="critic"
                        xml:id="note.7">Márton Kecseti.</note> et Blasio,<note type="critic"
                        xml:id="note.8">Balázs Péterváradi.</note> ut sacris initientur. Ego
                    postquam vocatione divina, Sacratissima Maiestas Vestra <del corresp="Olahus"
                        >me</del> hoc statu, in quo sum, clementer me providere dignata est, per
                    dominum <persName>Segniensem</persName>,<note type="critic" xml:id="note.9"
                        >Ferenc Jozefics.</note> quem hac de causa huc nunc accersivi, maiores
                    sacros ordines, hoc biduo ex Dei gratia ad summam Sacratissimam Maiestatem
                    Vestram Deus idem optimus maximus ad multa saecula felicem ac incolumem
                    conservare dignetur. In cuius clementiam me et fidelia <milestone unit="pb"
                    />servitia mea iterum atque iterum unice commendo.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.3">Ex <placeName>Vienna</placeName> prima Februarii anno 1549.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.4">
                    <seg type="signature">
                        <add corresp="Olahus" type="insert">Eiusdem Sacratissimae Maiestatis Vestrae
                            fidelis et humilis servitor, Agriensis</add>
                    </seg>
                </p>
                <pb/>
                <p xml:id="p.5">[2.] Si Sacratissima Maiestas Vestra in negotio provisionis
                        <persName>filii</persName><note type="critic" xml:id="note.10">John
                        Sigismund Szapolyai.</note> serenissimae reginae Isabellae a maiestate
                    caesarea aliquid responsi habet, dignetur ea in re ad commissarios suos, qui ad
                    festum beati Mathiae Apostoli<note type="critic" xml:id="note.11">24
                        February.</note><persName>fratrem Georgium</persName> conventuri sunt, dare
                    commissionem, ut Sacratissimae Maiestati Vestrae videbitur, simul vel divisim.
                    Dum <persName>Nadasdi</persName><note type="critic" xml:id="note.12">Tamás
                        Nádasdy.</note> unum ex commissariis hoc triduo huc exspecto. Is tamen de
                    expensarum inopia per litteras suas non parum apud me conqueritur. Cum quo de
                    his loquar, dum advenerit, bonum esset Sacratissimam Maiestatem Vestram
                    consiliariis camerae mandare, ut si aliter fieri non posset, providerent ei de
                    expensis honestis et convenientibus. Nam <persName>Nadasdi</persName> pro
                    dignitate Sacratissimae Maiestatis Vestrae ac conditione status sui atque
                    officii scribae expensas illas menstruas pro intertentione mensae ei designatas
                    in legatione hac, in qua authoritatis Maiestatis Vestrae Sacratissimae habenda
                    erit ratio, parum sibi suffecturas.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.6">
                    <seg type="signature">
                        <add corresp="Olahus" type="insert">Idem servitor Agriensis</add>
                    </seg>
                </p>
                <pb/>
            </div>
            <div style="handwritten" type="verso" xml:id="d.2">
                <head>On the outer side:</head>
                <p xml:id="p.7">Sacratissimae maiestati regiae Romanorum Hungariae et Boemiae etc.
                    domino, domino meo clementissimo.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
